#Text=Obama 's first State of the Union speech focuses on economy , jobs
#Text=Thursday , January 28 , 2010
#Text=President Barack Obama gives his State of the Union address to a joint session of Congress .
#Text=Image : Pete Souza .
#Text=AUDIO :
#Text=Listen to the entire State of the Union address ( 1:09:29 ) .

#Text=In his first annual State of the Union address Wednesday night , United States President Barack Obama urged Americans to overcome a deficit of trust in government and work together to solve a damaged economy and other problems .
#Text=Obama acknowledged that many Americans are frustrated and angry , doubting whether he can deliver the change he promised in his 2008 campaign .
#Text=But he said change is not easy , and he will continue to pursue it .

#Text=Let 's reject the false choice between protecting our people and upholding our values .

_	_	_	_

#Text=Another plan announced by Obama is to end the U.S. military 's controversial  do n't ask , do n't tell " policy on sexual orientation of service members that has existed since the Clinton administration saying , " This year , I will work with Congress and our military to finally repeal the law that denies gay Americans the right to serve the country they love because of who they are . "

column1: #Text=He added , " It 's the right thing to do . "

#Text=Obama also addressed the recent ruling by the Supreme Court of the United States in Citizens United v. Federal Election Commission saying , " With all due deference to separation of powers , last week the Supreme Court reversed a century of law that I believe will open the floodgates for special interests – including foreign corporations – to spend without limit in our elections . "
#Text=In a break of decorum , Associate Justice Samuel Alito appeared to mouth the words , " No , not true " , in response , according to many commentators .
#Text=File : Bob-McDonnell sm . jpg
#Text=Bob McDonnellImage : Nathan Muller .
#Text=( Image missing from commons : image ; log )
#Text=The Republican Party 's response to the president 's speech came from the governor of the state of Virginia , Bob McDonnell .
#Text=McDonnell gave the speech from the chamber of the Virginia House of Delegates .
#Text=He said Democrats are spending too much and causing an unsustainable level of debt .
#Text=The newly inaugurated governor said , " What government should not do is pile on more taxation , regulation and litigation that kill jobs and hurt the middle class . "
#Text=He also said Americans want affordable health care , but do not want the government to run it .
#Text=McDonnell also criticized the Obama administration 's handling of the suspect accused of trying to blow up Northwest Airlines Flight 253 on Christmas Day .
#Text=He said he does not agree with the decision to try the Nigerian suspect , Umar Farouk Abdulmutallab in the Detroit airliner plot in a U.S. civilian court .
#Text=McDonnell is one of several Republicans who have recently won elections in states which the Democrats swept in 2008 .
